      "lastUpdate": 1701947544306,
      "notes": "<img width=\"100%\" src=\"media://assets/snow02.jpg\" />\n\n<span style=\"color: #E4E6EB;\nfont-weight: 600; line-height:1.5;\n\">Category:</span> \nMultisensory Event\n\n<span style=\"color: #E4E6EB;\nfont-weight: 600;line-height:1.5;\n\">Design Intent:</span> \nConvey the feeling of a soft surface with some grittiness as the snow compacts under foot\n\n<span style=\"color: #E4E6EB;\nfont-weight: 600;line-height:2;\n\">Design Tips:</span> \nThe frequency is kept low to create a soft feeling. Modulating the frequency curve helps to further add texture.\n\n<span style=\"color: #FFF99;\nmargin: 8px 0px 12px;\nfont-size: 11px;\nfont-weight: 400;\nline-height: 16px;\ntext-transform: uppercase; line-height:2\"> Amplitude</span> \n<span style=\"\nfont-weight: 600;\n\">Resolution:</span> reduced by hand for smooth amplitude modulation between each emphasis peak. \n- Decreased the amplitude of the first onset\n- Increased amplitude of the tail and accentuated the tail peaks\n\n/newpage\n<span style=\"color: #FFFFFF99;\nmargin: 8px 0px 12px;\nfont-size: 11px;\nfont-weight: 400;\nline-height: 16px;\ntext-transform: uppercase; line-height:2;\"> Emphasis</span> \nAdded trailing emphasis points to the tail to create texture as the snow compacts under foot\n\n\n<span style=\"color: #FFFFFF99;\nmargin: 8px 0px 12px;\nfont-size: 11px;\nfont-weight: 400;\nline-height: 16px;\ntext-transform: uppercase; line-height:2;\">Frequency</span> \nThe frequency is kept low to create a soft feeling. Modulating the frequency curve helps to add some texture\n<span style=\"\nfont-weight: 600;\n\">Audio filter:</span> increased to 630Hz\n<span style=\"\nfont-weight: 600;\n\">Haptic Output:</span>   default\n",
