      "lastUpdate": 1701947617932,
      "notes": "<img width=\"100%\" src=\"media://assets/water02.jpg\" />\n\n<span style=\"color: #E4E6EB;\nfont-weight: 600; line-height:1.5;\n\">Category:</span> \nAmbient / Environment\n\n<span style=\"color: #E4E6EB;\nfont-weight: 600;line-height:1.5;\n\">Design Intent:</span> \nConvey the feeling of being close to water washing onto a shore. This is not an experience that one would directly  feel in real life but an abstract haptic experience that should convey relaxation and comfort.\n\n<span style=\"color: #E4E6EB;\nfont-weight: 600;line-height:1.5;\n\">Design Tips:</span> \n- The haptic envelope is modified heavily away from the audio envelope\n- This curation is made freeform by taking the original audio analysis and simplifying the breakpoints\n- The haptic waveform has been approximated by hand, using the rise and fall of water lapping as reference\n/newpage\n\n\n<span style=\"color: #FFF99;\nmargin: 8px 0px 12px;\nfont-size: 11px;\nfont-weight: 400;\nline-height: 16px;\ntext-transform: uppercase; line-height:2\"> \nAmplitude</span> \n<span style=\"\nfont-weight: 600;\n\">Gain:</span> increased to +14.5 dB to compensate for the original audio signal level\n<span style=\"\nfont-weight: 600;\n\">Resolution:</span> reduced to 10 bp/s for smooth amplitude modulation.\n\nThe amplitude curve was modified to follow the frequency curve. This translates into the feeling of rise and fall, swelling as the water laps at the shore.\n\n<span style=\"color: #FFFFFF99;\nmargin: 8px 0px 12px;\nfont-size: 11px;\nfont-weight: 400;\nline-height: 16px;\ntext-transform: uppercase; line-height:2;\">Emphasis</span> \n<span style=\"\nfont-weight: 600;\n\">Sensitivity:</span> reduced to 0% to remove emphasis points\n\n<span style=\"color: #FFFFFF99;\nmargin: 8px 0px 12px;\nfont-size: 11px;\nfont-weight: 400;\nline-height: 16px;\ntext-transform: uppercase; line-height:2;\">Frequency</span> \n<span style=\"\nfont-weight: 600;\n\">Audio Filter:</span>  increased to 950 Hz to lower the high frequency ceiling\n<span style=\"\nfont-weight: 600;\n\">Haptic Output:</span> default\n",
