      "lastUpdate": 1701947503304,
      "notes": "<img width=\"100%\" src=\"media://assets/hover.jpg\" />\n\n<span style=\"color: #E4E6EB;\nfont-weight: 600; line-height:1.5;\n\">Category:</span> \nStatic Interaction\n\n<span style=\"color: #E4E6EB;\nfont-weight: 600;line-height:1.5;\n\">Design Intent:</span> \nAs a single object is highlighted we want to create a smooth tactile feeling. When multiple tiles are selected in quick succession, the haptics should feel reassuring vs. intrusive.\n\nConsiderations:\n- Hover can be distracting when navigating quickly through menus\n- Audio/haptic/hover sync can be an issue, be sure to minimise this wherever possible\n- As this is a very repetitive gesture too much intensity or complexity can be distracting to the user and the experience\n- Be aware when combining all the elements above and design for a cohesive experience\n\n/newpage\n<span style=\"color: #E4E6EB;\nfont-weight: 600;line-height:2;\n\">Design Tips:</span> \nWe have used a low intensity ramp with a low frequency transient to emphasise the raised area\n\n<span style=\"color: #FFF99;\nmargin: 8px 0px 12px;\nfont-size: 11px;\nfont-weight: 400;\nline-height: 16px;\ntext-transform: uppercase; line-height:2\"> Amplitude</span> \n<span style=\"color: #FFFFFF99;\nfont-weight: 600;\n\">Gain</span>:  default\n<span style=\"color: #FFFFFF99;\nfont-weight: 600;\n\">Resolution:</span> default\n\n\n<span style=\"color: #FFFFFF99;\nmargin: 8px 0px 12px;\nfont-size: 11px;\nfont-weight: 400;\nline-height: 16px;\ntext-transform: uppercase; line-height:2;\"> Emphasis</span> \nAdded to the middle of the event to highlight the gesture\n\n<span style=\"color: #FFFFFF99;\nmargin: 8px 0px 12px;\nfont-size: 11px;\nfont-weight: 400;\nline-height: 16px;\ntext-transform: uppercase; line-height:2;\">Frequency</span> \nEnvelope follows the continuous waveform at low frequency to create a soft ramp \n<span style=\"\nfont-weight: 600;\n\">Audio filter:</span> default\n<span style=\"\nfont-weight: 600;\n\">Haptic Output:</span>   default\n",
